TASK-1 ğŸ® Hangman Game (Python)

ğŸ“Œ Project Overview This project is a simple text-based Hangman game developed using Python. The player must guess a hidden word one letter at a time within a limited number of attempts. The game runs entirely in the console and is designed for beginners to understand core programming concepts.

ğŸ¯ Objective To guess the randomly selected word correctly before running out of attempts.

âœ¨ Features Uses a predefined list of 5 words Random word selection using the random module Allows one-letter input at a time Maximum of 6 incorrect attempts Displays progress with underscores (_) for unguessed letters User-friendly messages for correct, incorrect, and repeated guesses

ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used Programming Language: Python Concepts Applied: Random module While loop If-else conditions Strings and lists User input and output

â–¶ï¸ How to Run the Project

Make sure Python is installed on your system.
Copy the code into a .py file (for example: hangman.py).
Open a terminal or command prompt.
Run the file using the command: python hangman.py
ğŸ® How to Play

The game selects a random word from the list.
You must guess the word by entering one letter at a time.
Correct guesses reveal the letter in the word.
Incorrect guesses reduce the remaining attempts.
You win if you guess all letters correctly.
You lose if all 6 attempts are used.
ğŸ† Winning Condition All letters in the secret word are guessed correctly before attempts reach zero.

ğŸ’€ Losing Condition Attempts become zero before guessing the full word.

ğŸ“š Learning Outcomes Understanding loops and conditionals Handling user input validation Working with lists and strings Implementing simple game logic in Python

Program:
import random

# List of predefined words
words = ["apple", "python", "cloud", "happy", "world"]

# Choose a random word
secret_word = random.choice(words)
guessed_letters = []
attempts = 6
print("ğŸ® Welcome to Hangman Game!")
print("Guess the word letter by letter.")
# Game loop
while attempts > 0:
    # Display current progress
    display_word = ""
    for letter in secret_word:
        if letter in guessed_letters:
            display_word += letter + " "
        else:
            display_word += "_ "
    print("\nWord:", display_word)

    # Check if player has guessed the word
    if all(letter in guessed_letters for letter in secret_word):
        print("\nğŸ‰ Congratulations! You guessed the word:", secret_word)
        break

    # Take input
    guess = input("Enter a letter: ").lower()

    # Validate input
    if len(guess) != 1 or not guess.isalpha():
        print("â— Please enter a single alphabet letter.")
        continue

    # Already guessed check
    if guess in guessed_letters:
        print("â— You already guessed that letter. Try another.")
        continue

    guessed_letters.append(guess)

    # Check guess
    if guess in secret_word:
        print("âœ” Good guess!")
    else:
        attempts -= 1
        print("âŒ Wrong guess! Attempts left:", attempts)

# Loss condition
if attempts == 0:
    print("\nğŸ’€ Game Over! The word was:", secret_word)

